com.facebook.react.turbomodule.core

Class TurboModuleManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.react.turbomodule.core.TurboModuleManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JSIModule, TurboModuleRegistry

    public class TurboModuleManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements JSIModule, TurboModuleRegistry
    This is the main class and entry point for TurboModules. Note that this is a hybrid class, and has a C++ counterpart This class installs the JSI bindings. It also implements the method to get a Java module, that the C++ counterpart calls.

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getEagerInitModuleNames()
        Description copied from interface: TurboModuleRegistry
        Return the names of all the NativeModules that are supposed to be eagerly initialized. By calling getModule on each name, this allows the application to eagerly initialize its NativeModules.
